# 📌 Project Work Allocation Document

## Train Tracking AI System

---

## 1. 📖 Overview

This document defines the **roles, responsibilities, and task allocation** for the development of the Train Tracking AI System. The goal is to ensure clear ownership, efficient collaboration, and successful delivery of all system components.

---

## 2. 👥 Team Members & Responsibilities

### 🧑‍💻 Ntando Badla

**Role:** Backend Developer & System Integration

**Responsibilities:**

* Develop and maintain the **Alerts System** (email notifications – already implemented, ensure stability and scalability)
* Design and manage the **database (Supabase)**:

  * User data (email, location)
  * Ticket history
  * Subscription data
* Handle **data updates and synchronization**:

  * Integrate scraped train data into the system
  * Ensure real-time updates are reflected accurately
* Build and maintain backend APIs:

  * `/register`
  * `/subscribe`
  * `/admin/update`
* Ensure **system performance, security, and error handling**

---

### 🧠 Semoshwe

**Role:** AI/ML Engineer (Sentiment Analysis)

**Responsibilities:**

* Develop the **Crowding & Safety Prediction System**
* Integrate:

  * Hugging Face models
  * VADER sentiment analysis
* Process input data (reviews, feedback, scraped text)
* Classify results into:

  * Crowd Level (Low / Medium / High)
  * Safety Rating (Safe / Moderate / Risky)
* Optimize model performance and accuracy
* Provide structured output for frontend display (charts, indicators)
* Collaborate with backend for API integration

---

### 🤖 Anita

**Role:** AI Chatbot Developer

**Responsibilities:**

* Design and implement the **AI Chatbot**
* Enable chatbot to:

  * Answer train availability questions
  * Explain delays
  * Recommend best train routes
* Integrate chatbot with:

  * Real-time train data
  * Sentiment analysis results (for smarter recommendations)
* Ensure conversational accuracy and user-friendly responses
* Handle chatbot API (`/chatbot`)
* Improve response quality and context handling

---

## 3. 🔗 Collaboration & Integration

* All team members must ensure their components are **API-driven and modular**
* Regular integration checkpoints must be conducted:

  * Backend ↔ Chatbot
  * Backend ↔ Sentiment Analysis
* Shared database (Supabase) must be consistently structured and documented
* Use version control (Git) for collaboration and tracking progress

---

## 4. 📅 Workflow & Communication

* Weekly progress updates
* Task tracking via shared tool ( GitHub )
* Immediate communication for blockers or integration issues

---

## 5. 🎯 Project Goal

To build a **scalable, AI-powered train tracking system** that delivers:

* Real-time updates
* Intelligent insights
* Automated notifications
* Enhanced commuter experience

---

## 6. ✅ Conclusion

This work allocation ensures that each team member has **clear ownership** of critical system components while encouraging collaboration across all modules. Successful coordination will result in a robust, efficient, and user-centered solution.

